example_bad:
fn main() {
    let mut v = vec![1, 2, 3];
    let first = &v[0];
    v.push(4); // Error: cannot borrow `v` as mutable
    println!("{}", first);
}

fixes.code:
let mut v = vec![1, 2, 3];
let first = &v[0];
println!("{}", first); // Use it here
v.push(4); // Now mutation is fine

let mut v = vec![1, 2, 3];
let first = v[0]; // Copy the i32 value
v.push(4);
println!("{}", first); // Works!
